<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Paul_Simon&action=edit&section=21.php.html" title="Edit section: Work on Broadway">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Work_on_Broadway">Work on Broadway</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><i>Rock 'N Roll! The First 5,000 Years</i> (1982) – <a href="Revue" title="Revue">revue</a> – featured songwriter for <a href="../Mrs._Robinson" title="Mrs. Robinson">Mrs. Robinson</a></li>
<li><i>Asinamali!</i> (1987) – play – co-<a href="Theatrical_producer" title="Theatrical producer">producer</a></li>
<li><i><a href="Mike_Nichols" title="Mike Nichols">Mike Nichols</a> and <a href="Elaine_May" title="Elaine May">Elaine May</a>: Together Again on Broadway</i> (1992) – <a href="Concert" title="Concert">concert</a> – performer</li>
<li><i><a href="The_Capeman" title="The Capeman">The Capeman</a></i> (1998) – <a href="Composer" title="Composer">composer</a>, co-<a href="Lyricist" title="Lyricist">lyricist</a> and <a href="Arrangement" title="Arrangement">music arranger</a> – <a href="Tony_Award" title="Tony Award">Tony</a> Nomination for <a href="Tony_Award_for_Best_Original_Score" title="Tony Award for Best Original Score">Best Original Score</a></li>
<li><i><a href="The_Graduate" title="The Graduate">The Graduate</a></i> (2002) – play – featured songwriter</li>
</ul>
